whats the best lcd tv for video games samsung has a game mode on many of their lcd tv's basically game mode turns off any processing that the tv does so that the picture is instantly transmitted from the game box to the screen processing can cause a delay which takes away from the game play i think samsung is the only manufacturer on the market that actually allows you to disable their video processing for the purpose of better game play Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Liquid crystal display television Handheld game console Computer display TFT LCD IBM PC compatible Liquid crystal display Atari 8-bit family MSX Oscilloscope Television Game Boy Advance Windows XP Pixel Organic light-emitting diode Universal Serial Bus Sega Saturn PlayStation Portable Photography Stereoscopy Game Boy Sega Xbox Nintendo Entertainment System Nintendo Digital photography IMac Random access memory High-definition television DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution 7thMIX Spider-Man (games) Canon T90 Sega Dreamcast Commodore 64 Sinclair ZX81 Commodore International Metroid Prime: Hunters Guilty Gear Hard disk ZX Spectrum Blu-ray Disc Mouse (computing) TurboGrafx 16 Acorn Computers Nintendo DS Samsung Multiplayer ATI Technologies SCART Musical Instrument Digital Interface Amstrad CPC PowerBook Amstrad DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution 6thMIX Game Boy Color SAM Coup__ RISC Atari ST Teletext Super Nintendo Entertainment System The Legend of Zelda series Xbox 360 Atari 2600 Interlace Commodore 128 Advance Wars: Dual Strike Computer role-playing game Computer and video games Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Amiga Color Graphics Adapter Radeon Modem Minesweeper (computer game) Laptop History of computer and video games Light-emitting diode Apple II family Pop'n Music Computer and video game genres Pac-Man Bally Astrocade Cyberspace Screensaver GunBound Palm OS Acorn Electron Konica Minolta Dance Dance Revolution ULTRAMIX DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution Integrated Services Digital Broadcasting Counter-Strike Gamu